                                <code>.accordion-body</code>, though the transition does limit overflow.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h4 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                        Accordion Item #2
                    </h4>
                    <div class="accordion-item">

                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingTwo"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <strong>This is the second item's accordion body.</strong> It is hidden by default,
                                until
                                the collapse plugin adds the appropriate classes that we use to style each element.
                                These
                                classes control the overall appearance, as well as the showing and hiding via CSS
                                transitions. You can modify any of this with custom CSS or overriding our default
                                variables.
                                It's also worth noting that just about any HTML can go within the
                                <code>.accordion-body</code>, though the transition does limit overflow.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h4 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                        Accordion Item #3
                    </h4>
                    <div class="accordion-item">

                        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingThree"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <strong>This is the third item's accordion body.</strong> It is hidden by default, until
                                the
                                collapse plugin adds the appropriate classes that we use to style each element. These
                                classes control the overall appearance, as well as the showing and hiding via CSS
                                transitions. You can modify any of this with custom CSS or overriding our default
                                variables.
                                It's also worth noting that just about any HTML can go within the
                                <code>.accordion-body</code>, though the transition does limit overflow.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <br>
                <div class="privilege-program__content js-privilege-program">
                    <a class="privilege-program__link" href="/sale/online/?privilege=1&amp;action=paging&amp;utm_source=glavnaya&amp;utm_medium=saydbar&amp;utm_campaign=programma_privilegiy" target="_blank"></a>
                    <div class="privilege-program__text">
                        Товары со скидками							</div>
                    <div class="privilege-program__info">

                        <div class="privilege-program__discount">
                            <div class="privilege-program__prefix">
                                <div class="privilege-program__text-prefix">до</div>
                                <div class="privilege-program__minus-prefix">-</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="privilege-program__number">40</div>
                            <div class="privilege-program__percent">%</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}
        {% set col = 'col-9' %}
        {% if app.request.get('_route') == 'cart' %}
            {% set col = 'col-12' %}
        {% endif %}
        <div class="{{ col }}">
            <div class="content">
                {% block newstop_body %}{% endblock %}

            </div>

            <div id="last-post" class="col-10">
                <div class="container">
                    <h3>Последние статьи</h3>
                    <ul>
                        {% for news in newstop %}
                            <li><a href="{{ path('newstop.show', { slug: news.slug }) }}">{{ news }}</a></li>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
{% block javascripts %}

    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('checkout') }}
{% endblock %}
</div>

